# Files NOT to copy into the Docker image.
#
# Note the Dockerfile now does `COPY src /app`, so anything outside src/ is
# already excluded from the build context that gets into the image. This
# file mostly exists to keep the daemon-side build context small (faster
# `docker compose build`) and to defensively block things that might creep
# into src/ during development (pycache, .DS_Store).

# Virtualenv (we install fresh inside the image)
.venv/
venv/

# Local SQLite DB and its journal files (lives at project root; bind-mounted
# at runtime via docker-compose.yml).
data.db
data.db-journal
data.db-wal
data.db-shm

# Raw broker exports — host-only.
downloaded/

# Logs — host-only.
logs/

# Real env file with secrets. Only the .example template ships in the image.
.env
.env.*
!.env.runtime.example

# Docker-mode user data dir (host bind mount at runtime).
phoenix-data/

# Git internals
.git/
.gitignore

# Python cache + build artefacts (defensive — would only show up if cached
# in src/ on the host).
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
*.egg-info/
build/
dist/

# IDE / editor / OS junk
.idea/
.vscode/
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.swp
*~
*.tmp.*
.claude/

# Backup files
*.bak

# Host-side directories not needed at runtime (the LICENSE file IS needed
# but it's bind-mounted in docker-compose.yml, not baked into the image).
docs/
scripts/
README.md
LICENSE
Dockerfile
docker-compose.yml
